The paper discusses the use of deep learning for control problems, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on robotic arm manipulation, robot navigation, and autonomous vehicles, which are all topics within the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the difficulties of validating the safety of deep control policies, which is a topic within the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses neural networks for autonomous driving, which is a topic within the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV).
